# Python Commands Via Virtualenv

- Always run Python-related commands using the project virtual environment at `.venv`.
- Use `.venv/bin/python` for Python execution instead of system `python` or `python3`.
- Use `.venv/bin/pip` for package installation instead of global `pip`.
- Run tests as `.venv/bin/python -m pytest ...` (or `.venv/bin/pytest ...` if needed).
- For tools (formatters/linters), prefer `.venv/bin/<tool>` or `.venv/bin/python -m <tool>`.

Examples:
- `.venv/bin/python -m pytest`
- `.venv/bin/python -m ruff check .`
- `.venv/bin/python script.py`
